Class Ft

FtWt
public class Ft
extends java.lang.Object
implements DeepCopyable

This represents the concept 'Filtration', the information available at time t.

The information can include, for example,

  • time
  • value of the stochastic process
  • values of the driving Brownian motion(s)

See Also:
"Fima C. Klebaner. Introduction to Stochastic Calculus with Applications. 2nd ed. pp.23. Imperial College Press. 2006."

dWt

public double dWt()
Get the increment of the driving Brownian motion during the time differential.

This is the product of the Gaussian distribution innovation and the square root of the time differential.

Returns:
the increment of the driving Brownian motion during the time differential
